This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with improving the accuracy of sequence to sequence models in machine translation and abstractive summarization. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes an unsupervised learning method to improve supervised models. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with improving the generalization of seq2seq models. 

It may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses neural networks for the seq2seq models. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as abstractive summarization involves understanding and summarizing visual content.
